Jenna Etheridge, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Two children were killed when a van knocked them down in Soweto on Wednesday afternoon, Johannesburg metro police said.The boy, 5, and the girl, 7, had been walking home from school on the sidewalk of Dlamini Road in Kliptown, Chief Superintendent Wayne Minnaar said.A 62-year-old man lost control of his white Tata van and struck them. He was arrested and charged with two counts of culpable homicide, and reckless or negligent driving.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.